  <prompt>
    Extend the Daily Briefing hook (`useDailyBriefing.ts`) and section component (`DailyBriefingSection.tsx`)
    from task 034 with three failure / empty paths per FR-16 + NFR-11:
    (a) 429 response from `POST /api/ai/daily-briefing/narrate` → render a graceful degraded card with
        a retry CTA; section stays visible; does NOT block rest of workspace from rendering (NFR-11).
        Emit `spaarke-ai-error.daily-briefing-429` telemetry via the helper from task 013 (FR-24).
    (b) Empty result (no tasks, no records, no notifications) → render a friendly empty state:
        small icon + "Nothing to see right now — enjoy your day" (OC-08). Section remains visible.
    (c) Success — unchanged from task 034.
    No happy-path telemetry events (FR-24 strict).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent UI v9 frontend developer wiring resilient AI-data-consuming UX. Bias toward
    keeping the section visible across all three states (success / 429 / empty); never hide; use
    Fluent v9 tokens for the degraded + empty visuals; emit error telemetry only at the 429 boundary.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `DailyBriefingSection.tsx` renders correctly in three states:
    - SUCCESS: AI bullets in a Fluent v9 Card (unchanged from task 034).
    - 429: A degraded card with explanatory message + retry button; section remains visible; emits
      `spaarke-ai-error.daily-briefing-429` telemetry once per failure (not per render).
    - EMPTY: A friendly empty card with small icon + "Nothing to see right now — enjoy your day";
      section remains visible; NO telemetry (it's not an error).
    No happy-path telemetry events emitted anywhere.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-16 + NFR-11 + OC-08 together define the three-state Daily Briefing UX. The 429 path must
      degrade gracefully without blocking the rest of the workspace (per NFR-11 — Daily Briefing is
      one of N sections and its failure must not cascade). Empty state is friendly, NOT an error
      (per OC-08). FR-24 is strict: this project emits error-only telemetry — no happy-path
      events. The telemetry helper module is built in task 013; this task consumes it.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/useDailyBriefing.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/DailyBriefingSection.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">No new BFF service. The 429 / empty handling is frontend-only — consumes the existing endpoint shape.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">TTL cache from task 034 stays in effect. On 429, do NOT poison the cache with the error — leave the previous successful response cached (if any) so it returns on the next read.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016">Rate-limit handling per the ADR — surface 429 gracefully; do NOT auto-retry with backoff in this task (the user retries manually via the CTA).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Use Fluent v9 tokens only. NO hex literals, NO `rgba(...)` literals. The degraded card + empty card must adapt to dark mode by construction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-025">Empty-state icon and retry-CTA icon from `@fluentui/react-icons` (v9). No new SVG.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No change to auth contract. `authenticatedFetch` remains the single auth surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">FR-24 — emit ONLY error events. NO happy-path events. The empty state is NOT an error and gets NO telemetry. Only the 429 path emits `spaarke-ai-error.daily-briefing-429`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NFR-11 — Daily Briefing failure (429) must NOT block the rest of the workspace from rendering. The section degrades in place; sibling sections render normally.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">OC-08 empty-state copy is hardcoded English: "Nothing to see right now — enjoy your day". Do not localize (OC-10 — English only).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Telemetry deduplication — emit `spaarke-ai-error.daily-briefing-429` ONCE per failure event, not per render. Avoid emit-loops on re-renders.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-014-ai-caching.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-016-ai-rate-limits.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/bff-url-normalization.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/full-page-custom-page.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/WORKSPACE-AI-PREFILL-GUIDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Extend useDailyBriefing to surface typed error state">
      Edit `useDailyBriefing.ts` to ensure the hook returns a typed error discriminator:
      `error: { kind: 'rate-limit' } | { kind: 'other'; message?: string } | null`.
      When fetch returns HTTP 429, set `error = { kind: 'rate-limit' }`. For other errors, set
      `{ kind: 'other', ... }`. Detect empty response (no items in payload — match the contract
      from spec.md OC-08 / FR-16: no tasks, no records, no notifications) and surface `data` as
      an empty array (NOT null) so the component can distinguish empty vs. error.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Render degraded card with retry on 429">
      Edit `DailyBriefingSection.tsx`. When `error.kind === 'rate-limit'`, render a Fluent v9 Card
      with:
      - A short explanatory message (e.g., "Daily Briefing temporarily unavailable — try again in a moment.")
      - A "Retry" button (Fluent v9 `Button`) that re-invokes the hook (e.g., calls a `refetch`
        function exposed by `useDailyBriefing` — add this if not already present).
      The section does NOT collapse; it stays visible at the same dimensions as the success state.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Detect and render empty state">
      When `data` is an empty array (no bullets), render a friendly empty state:
      - Small icon (e.g., `EmojiSparkleRegular` or `InfoRegular` from `@fluentui/react-icons`)
      - Copy: "Nothing to see right now — enjoy your day" (hardcoded English per OC-10)
      Section remains visible at the same dimensions; NO telemetry emitted.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Emit 429 telemetry via task-013 helper">
      Import the error-only telemetry helper from task 013 (the helper module wired to App Insights).
      On transition into the 429 state, emit `spaarke-ai-error.daily-briefing-429` ONCE per failure
      (use a `useRef` flag or only emit inside the `useEffect` that handles error transitions —
      avoid emit-on-every-render). Include relevant properties as the helper's schema supports
      (e.g., `endpoint`, `userId` if available, `timestamp`).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Test all three states locally">
      (a) Success: confirm normal bullets render unchanged from task 034.
      (b) 429: mock the endpoint to return 429 (via dev tools network override or a test fixture).
          Confirm degraded card + retry button render; click retry → re-fetch; sibling sections in
          the layout continue rendering normally (NFR-11).
      (c) Empty: mock the endpoint to return an empty payload. Confirm "Nothing to see right now —
          enjoy your day" + icon render; widget stays visible.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify dark mode parity for all three states">
      Toggle dark mode. Confirm all three states (success, 429, empty) render correctly with no
      hex / rgba literals. Empty-state icon must adapt color (use `currentColor` or tokens).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify telemetry deduplication">
      In dev tools, force two consecutive 429 responses + intervening renders. Confirm
      `spaarke-ai-error.daily-briefing-429` is emitted ONCE per failure transition (not on each
      render). Use App Insights local sink or console.log instrumentation to verify.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Confirm NFR-11 — Daily Briefing 429 does not block rest of workspace">
      With Daily Briefing in 429 state, verify other sections in the same layout still render
      normally. The Workspace pane stays usable; user can switch tabs; other widgets work.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Update TASK-INDEX and commit">
      Update `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: this task's status
      to ✅ completed. Commit changes per project conventions.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read existing useDailyBriefing.ts + DailyBriefingSection.tsx from task 034; read telemetry helper module from task 013</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Extend hook with typed error + refetch; extend component with 3-state rendering + telemetry emission</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Verify no happy-path telemetry calls; no hex/rgba literals</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">npm build + lint verification</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/useDailyBriefing.ts (modified — typed error + refetch)</output>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/DailyBriefingSection.tsx (modified — three-state rendering + telemetry)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">When `POST /api/ai/daily-briefing/narrate` returns 429, the section renders a degraded card with a Retry button; section remains visible at its normal dimensions (does not collapse).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Clicking Retry re-invokes the hook (refetch is observable in DevTools Network tab).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Sibling sections in the layout continue rendering normally while Daily Briefing is in 429 state (NFR-11).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">When the endpoint returns an empty payload, the section renders an empty state: small icon + literal text "Nothing to see right now — enjoy your day".</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Empty state stays visible (does not hide the widget).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`spaarke-ai-error.daily-briefing-429` is emitted to App Insights exactly once per 429 failure event (not per render); verified via App Insights or the telemetry helper's debug sink.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No happy-path telemetry events are emitted anywhere in `useDailyBriefing.ts` or `DailyBriefingSection.tsx` (grep confirms no calls to the telemetry helper outside the 429 path).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All three states (success, 429, empty) render correctly in dark mode; zero hex / rgba literals in the modified files.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` succeeds with zero TypeScript errors and zero new lint warnings.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Daily Briefing 429 Degraded Card (FR-16, NFR-11)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=spaarke_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Navigate to the SpaarkeAi code page with a layout that includes Daily Briefing and at least one sibling section</step>
        <step>In DevTools Network panel, override `POST /api/ai/daily-briefing/narrate` to return HTTP 429</step>
        <step>Reload the page</step>
        <step>Verify Daily Briefing renders the degraded card with a Retry button (section remains visible at normal dimensions)</step>
        <step>Verify sibling sections render normally (Daily Briefing does NOT block rest of workspace)</step>
        <step>Click Retry; verify another fetch occurs in Network panel</step>
        <step>Check App Insights / telemetry sink for one `spaarke-ai-error.daily-briefing-429` event</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Degraded card renders with retry. Sibling sections unaffected. One telemetry event per 429 failure.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Daily Briefing Empty State (FR-16, OC-08)">
      <steps>
        <step>Mock `POST /api/ai/daily-briefing/narrate` to return an empty payload (no tasks, no records, no notifications)</step>
        <step>Reload the workspace</step>
        <step>Verify Daily Briefing renders: small icon + literal text "Nothing to see right now — enjoy your day"</step>
        <step>Verify the widget stays visible (does not collapse or hide)</step>
        <step>Verify NO telemetry event is emitted for the empty state (not an error)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Empty state shows friendly icon + OC-08 copy. Widget remains visible. No telemetry emitted.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Dark Mode Parity for All Three States (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode in D365 settings</step>
        <step>Verify success state renders correctly in dark mode</step>
        <step>Verify 429 degraded card (with retry button) renders correctly in dark mode</step>
        <step>Verify empty state (icon + copy) renders correctly in dark mode — icon uses currentColor or tokens</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>All three states render correctly in dark mode. No hex / rgba regressions.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

